## HHSection1('Local Linearity and the Differential')

Context("Numeric");
Context()->variables->add( y=>'Real', 'dx'=>'Real', 'dy'=>'Real' );
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$v1 = list_random('x', 'y');
$v2 = ( $v1 eq 'x' ) ? 'y' : 'x';

$x0 = ( $v1 eq 'x' ) ? 0 : non_zero_random(-3,3,1);
$y0 = ( $v1 eq 'y' ) ? 0 : non_zero_random(-3,3,1);

$whichf = list_random(0,1);
if ( $whichf ) {
    $f = Compute( "$v2*e^{$v1}" );
} else {
    $f = Compute( "$v2*e^{-$v1}" );
}

$fx = $f->D('x');
$fx0 = $fx->eval( x=>$x0, y=>$y0 );
$fy = $f->D('y');
$fy0 = $fy->eval( x=>$x0, y=>$y0 );
$df = Compute( "($fx0)*dx + ($fy0)*dy" );

Context()->texStrings;
TEXT(beginproblem());
BEGIN_TEXT

Find the differential of the function
\( f(x,y) = $f \) at \( ($x0,$y0) \).

$PAR
\( df = \) \{ ans_rule(35) \}

END_TEXT
Context()->normalStrings;

ANS( $df->cmp() );

Context()->texStrings;
SOLUTION(EV3(<<'END_SOLUTION'));
$PAR SOLUTION $PAR

We have \( df = f_x \, dx + f_y \, dy\).
Finding the partial derivatives, we have
\( f_x = $fx\), so \(f_x($x0,$y0) = $fx0\), and
\( f_y = $fy\), so \(f_y($x0,$y0) = $fy0\).
Thus, \( df = $df\).

END_SOLUTION
Context()->normalStrings;

ENDDOCUMENT();
